<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

Our team ran business sites on SiteGround for three years before switching to Kinsta. Both hosted WordPress sites for venue partners and marketing sites. The switch wasn't because SiteGround was bad — it wasn't. It was because Kinsta's performance difference was measurable and the support experience was noticeably better.

<p><strong>Kinsta</strong> is managed WordPress hosting built on Google Cloud Platform. Premium pricing, premium performance, premium support. Every site gets its own isolated container, automatic daily backups, staging environments, and a CDN.</p>

<p><strong>SiteGround</strong> is shared hosting that punches above its weight. Good performance for the price, solid uptime, decent support, and WordPress-specific features like auto-updates and caching.</p>

<h2 id="performance">Performance: Kinsta Wins</h2>

This is the biggest difference and the reason I switched.

<p><strong>Kinsta's infrastructure:</strong> Each site runs in its own isolated LXD container on Google Cloud Platform. You get dedicated resources -- no other site on the server can affect your performance. Google's network (one of the fastest in the world) handles the routing. The built-in Cloudflare CDN serves assets from 260+ global edge locations.</p>

<p><strong>SiteGround's infrastructure:</strong> Shared hosting on Google Cloud (they migrated a few years ago). Performance is good for shared hosting, but you're sharing server resources with other accounts. Their SuperCacher helps, but under load you'll feel the difference.</p>

<p><strong>Real-world difference:</strong> Our marketing site loaded in 1.2 seconds on SiteGround. On Kinsta, same site, same content: 0.6 seconds. The venue partner sites showed similar improvements. For sites where page speed affects SEO rankings and user experience, that difference matters.</p>

<p><strong>Uptime:</strong> Both are reliable. Kinsta guarantees 99.9% uptime with an SLA. SiteGround guarantees 99.9% as well. In practice, I experienced one brief outage on SiteGround in three years and zero on Kinsta in two years.</p>

<h2 id="pricing">Pricing: SiteGround Wins</h2>

This is where SiteGround has a clear advantage.

