The gap is significant. For operators hosting 3-5 simple venue sites, SiteGround's GrowBig plan at $5/mo handles all of them. The equivalent on Kinsta would cost $70-115/mo.

<p><strong>Important caveat:</strong> SiteGround's promotional pricing jumps significantly on renewal. The $5/mo GrowBig plan renews at $25/mo. Kinsta's pricing stays the same. Still cheaper, but the gap narrows.</p>

<p><strong>The value question:</strong> Is Kinsta worth 3-10x more than SiteGround? For a marketing site where page speed directly affects lead generation and SEO rankings -- yes. For simple informational venue pages that get a few hundred visits per month -- probably not.</p>

<h2 id="support">Support: Kinsta Wins</h2>

Kinsta's support is the best I've experienced in WordPress hosting. Every conversation starts with a knowledgeable WordPress engineer, not a first-tier script reader. Average response time is under 2 minutes via live chat. They proactively monitor your site and will reach out if they detect performance issues.

SiteGround's support is good by shared hosting standards. You'll talk to knowledgeable agents who can solve most WordPress issues. But the response time is slower (5-15 minutes typical), and complex problems sometimes require escalation.

For operators managing multiple sites who don't want to troubleshoot hosting issues themselves, Kinsta's support quality justifies a significant portion of the premium.

