Kinsta's custom dashboard (MyKinsta) is cleaner and more powerful than SiteGround's Site Tools. The built-in APM (Application Performance Monitor) lets you diagnose slow queries, plugins, and page load issues without installing third-party tools. For operators troubleshooting site performance across multiple venues, this visibility is valuable.

<h2 id="multi-location">Multi-Location Considerations</h2>

If you're hosting separate WordPress sites for each venue location:

<p><strong>Kinsta approach:</strong> Each site gets its own container with guaranteed resources. Performance is consistent regardless of how many sites you're running. But the cost scales per site -- 10 venue sites on Kinsta's Business 1 plan runs $115/mo.</p>

<p><strong>SiteGround approach:</strong> All sites share resources on one account. Performance is good but variable under load. The cost is flat -- unlimited sites on GrowBig at $5-25/mo (promo vs renewal).</p>

<p><strong>My recommendation:</strong> Use Kinsta for your primary business site (the one driving leads and revenue) and SiteGround for simple venue informational pages. That gives you premium performance where it matters and budget hosting where it doesn't.</p>

